Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.25,0:00:05.05,title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(573.545,152.727)\fad(500,850)\bord5\blur20}Mushishi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.25,0:00:05.05,ep-title,,0,0,5,,{\fad(500,850)\bord5\blur10}Interview with the Director
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.12,0:00:20.03,sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)\blur5\4c&HF7F603&\c&HFFF9BF&\t(0,1200,\4c&H47801F&\c&H00000&)}What was your first encounter with 'Mushishi' like?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.50,0:00:10.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you could say
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.34,0:00:13.26,dialogue,,0,0,0,,that I first encountered it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.26,0:00:18.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,when I picked up the manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.00,0:00:28.64,dialogue,,0,0,0,,When glancing at the cover of the manga,\NI couldn't tell what the story was about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.53,0:00:38.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the kanji characters\Nfor "Mushishi" were quite powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.20,0:00:43.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that had a big impact on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.87,0:00:49.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cover has just the title\Nand a man whose name is Ginko;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.48,0:00:54.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,it looked very different to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.15,0:00:58.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't tell what it was from the cover.\NI couldn't tell what it was about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.82,0:01:03.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that made the shock\NI got when I read it bigger...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.83,0:01:10.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,since I read it when I didn't\Nknow what it was about.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.27,0:01:16.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It turned out that, how should I put it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.47,0:01:21.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's not something that\Ndeals with good and evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.81,0:01:26.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not something that\Nportrays only happy endings.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.85,0:01:30.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not something that\Nfocuses only on characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.52,0:01:35.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not something that\Nemphasizes story settings too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.53,0:01:41.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Mushishi manga is something\Nthat's really close to the feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.53,0:01:44.20,dialogue,,0,0,0,,of meeting and talking with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.20,0:01:48.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think the manga fans\Nprobably feel this way about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.80,0:01:53.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you meet someone for the first\Ntime, you say, "How do you do?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.14,0:01:58.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't know what this person is like,\Nbut you start talking about things,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.15,0:02:03.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,like "Oh, you like this?"\Nor "Oh, I play this sport, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.15,0:02:07.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you talk with this person,\Nyou end up learning more about him/her,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.16,0:02:10.19,dialogue,,0,0,0,,like, "Oh, he/she likes this one, too,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.19,0:02:13.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,or "Oh, he/she gets upset if others\Ndo this kind of thing to him/her."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.83,0:02:17.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, there're many things that you'll\Nlearn as you socialize with this person.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.50,0:02:21.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Mushishi manga\Ngave me a similar impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.84,0:02:26.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you read on, you'll learn, "Oh, Ginko\Ngets worked up in this kind of situation."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.18,0:02:31.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, "Oh, there's mushi like this."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.51,0:02:35.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like this, you'll discover new things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.48,0:02:38.72,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if you read it at\Ndifferent times in your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.72,0:02:42.19,dialogue,,0,0,0,,you'll be surprised to find\Nthings that you missed before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.19,0:02:51.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a manga that makes you notice\Nmany things that you overlooked before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.68,0:03:03.66,sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)\blur5\4c&HF7F603&\c&HFFF9BF&\t(0,1200,\4c&H47801F&\c&H00000&)}What do you keep in mind when animating 'Mushishi'?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.14,0:02:57.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just to make it exactly like the manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.81,0:03:02.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like manga books.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.48,0:03:04.06,dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.08,0:03:09.02,dialogue,,0,0,0,,when a manga I liked was animated,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.02,0:03:13.31,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't enjoy it that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.31,0:03:19.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I always thought things like,\N"Oh, no! They changed it like that?" or
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.81,0:03:25.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I liked this part, but they omitted it..."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.19,0:03:30.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I thought, "When I create a show,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.04,0:03:35.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,especially since it is a wonderful\Nwork that I became attached to,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.68,0:03:41.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I absolutely don't want\Nto twist things around."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.52,0:03:45.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really want people\Nto have the same feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.94,0:03:49.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,no matter which one they experience\Nfirst, the manga or the anime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.34,0:03:52.61,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to create it\Nso that there is no difference
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.61,0:03:55.18,dialogue,,0,0,0,,between reading the manga\Nand watching the anime,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.18,0:04:00.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,so that it won't make a difference even if people go back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.75,0:04:04.24,dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that sense, I'd make\Nabsolutely no changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.24,0:04:06.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd add no strange modifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.48,0:04:11.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I didn't want it to be\Njust an imitation of the manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:14.98,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, of course, while carefully thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.98,0:04:19.98,dialogue,,0,0,0,,about what would be needed and\Nwhat I should do to make animation,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.32,0:04:27.03,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I should focus\Non creating animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.03,0:04:29.67,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I paid attention to that part a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.52,0:04:42.16,sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)\blur5\4c&HF7F603&\c&HFFF9BF&\t(0,1200,\4c&H47801F&\c&H00000&)}What is the highlight of 'Mushishi'\Nand what was challenging about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.50,0:04:35.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The highlight of the show...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.44,0:04:39.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,is the expression of the "Mushishi" world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.51,0:04:44.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The background art, light, and water...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.85,0:04:51.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those things are common to our world...\Nthings that you find anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.79,0:04:56.79,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The air the characters\Nbreath in. The raindrops...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.09,0:05:02.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone treats these things\Nvery, very carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.13,0:05:07.79,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Waki-san, who is the art director,\NHama-san, who is the shooting director,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.80,0:05:10.24,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tanaka-san, who is the sound director,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.22,0:05:12.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okuda-san, who is\Nin charge of sound effects...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.29,0:05:14.89,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone pursues the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.89,0:05:20.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if I am to say what\Nthe highlight is, that would be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.47,0:05:24.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The world of "Mushi-shi" is also the highlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.27,0:05:26.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The staff thinks that you\Nprobably don't often see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.56,0:05:34.65,dialogue,,0,0,0,,this kind of world expression\Nin anime these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.83,0:05:39.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we've been creating the show\Nwith this idea that shows like Mushishi,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.90,0:05:43.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,which focus on the world, are rare,\Nthe world is really the highlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:50.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Things that were challenging...\NEspecially for the staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.11,0:05:57.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,for example, there's a scene that\Nshows the movement of mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.02,0:06:05.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We needed about 1000 pages\Nfor 6 or 7 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.46,0:06:08.26,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The animators had to draw\Nthem all in detail by hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.26,0:06:14.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They draw the movement little by little,\Nso I think that's a lot of work,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.47,0:06:19.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I don't think that's\Nsomething that was challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.81,0:06:24.14,dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, I read the manga.\NI keep in mind to read the manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.15,0:06:28.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I read the original work... That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.48,0:06:31.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if you like the manga,\Nall you need to do is just read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.15,0:06:39.31,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if I say it that way, it sounds\Nlike I'm doing it without thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.83,0:06:43.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the toughest thing may be
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.75,0:06:50.06,dialogue,,0,0,0,,when I have to convey the good part\Nof this work to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.44,0:06:53.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, "In this episode,\Nthis is the good part," or
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.44,0:06:58.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"In this episode, this action by the\Nepisode's main character was interesting."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.78,0:07:03.45,dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's actually quicker for them to\Nunderstand it if they read the manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.45,0:07:07.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it'd be quicker if I ask\Nthem all to sit down and read it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.12,0:07:11.13,dialogue,,0,0,0,,since several hundred people\Nare involved in the project,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:16.13,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't force them all to read it.\NThey all have limited time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.13,0:07:21.13,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There're, of course, people\Nwho work on things that we present.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.14,0:07:28.56,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a type of work\Nwhose appeal is hard to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.28,0:07:36.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and is easier to understand if you\Nread the manga or watch the anime,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.34,0:07:44.71,dialogue,,0,0,0,,so when I have to explain the\Nappeal of "Mushishi" to people,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.99,0:07:47.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,you can probably say its tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.81,0:07:59.83,sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)\blur5\4c&HF7F603&\c&HFFF9BF&\t(0,1200,\4c&H47801F&\c&H00000&)}Please tell us about the 'Mushishi' staff
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.43,0:07:53.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Producing animation is a team effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.77,0:08:01.76,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's something that you won't see the\Ncompleted product if someone is absent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.78,0:08:06.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're creating this series at an anime\Nproduction company called Artland.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.12,0:08:17.11,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The staff members are incredibly\Ncommitted to the project.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.13,0:08:21.31,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see that in the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.31,0:08:31.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I feel really lucky that I am able to\Nproduce this show at a company like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.14,0:08:34.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, I can say this for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.81,0:08:41.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umakoshi-san, Waki-san, Sugawara-san,\Nwhose photos were used in the opening,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.82,0:08:45.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masuda-san, who was\Nin charge of the music...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.75,0:08:50.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every single piece of work\Nthat has been completed has...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.04,0:08:59.76,dialogue,,0,0,0,,how should I put it, the power\Nof the original work in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.44,0:09:03.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no exaggeration to say
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.47,0:09:08.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,that everything is thanks\Nto the power of all the staff members.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.78,0:09:11.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.50,0:09:24.51,sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)\blur5\4c&HF7F603&\c&HFFF9BF&\t(0,1200,\4c&H47801F&\c&H00000&)}Have there been any\N'just between you and me' stories\Nwhile working on 'Mushishi'?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.11,0:09:18.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Just between you and me" stories while working on "Mushishi"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.12,0:09:22.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I create the DVD jackets
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.32,0:09:25.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,with Umakoshi-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.39,0:09:29.41,dialogue,,0,0,0,,we have one little story line\Nthat we base them on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.41,0:09:37.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You might not find this interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.14,0:09:41.14,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a simple thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.14,0:09:49.90,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The jacket for DVD volume 1\Nshows Ginko walking towards you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.15,0:09:59.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, the jackets after that show\NGinko sitting down, looking around, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.95,0:10:06.42,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We draw them based on a story line\Nthat Umakoshi-san and I decided on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.17,0:10:12.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We decided not to tell anyone about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.84,0:10:19.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You asked me for "just between you\Nand me" stories, so here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.85,0:10:24.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right... we designed the DVD jackets\Nbased on one story line.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.80,0:10:29.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another story is about...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.86,0:10:42.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}[ kago = cage ]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.86,0:10:42.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Artland created an annex office called\N"Mushi-Kago" for the Mushi-shi project.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.87,0:10:44.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's just an ordinary house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.87,0:10:49.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone works upstairs there,\Nand I work downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.15,0:10:58.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I get really busy with work,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.82,0:11:03.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I put a futon on the floor and sleep there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.83,0:11:08.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the staff doesn't show\Nany consideration...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.16,0:11:19.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even when I'm sleeping, I'm awakened\Nby loud noises from the photocopier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.51,0:11:23.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, even when I say,\N"it's really freezing downstairs,"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.85,0:11:28.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,they'd just say, "Oh, really?\Nit's been like that lately".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.58,0:11:33.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They have one of the latest\Nheating/AC units upstairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.09,0:11:37.11,dialogue,,0,0,0,,so it's very warm there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.11,0:11:40.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, it's very cool during\Nthe hottest days in the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.86,0:11:45.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have an old heating/AC unit\Nfrom long ago downstairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.94,0:11:49.14,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't work at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.14,0:11:57.26,dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I set the heater for about\N30°C (86°F), it finally warms up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.48,0:12:04.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess many people probably\Nwanted to hear fun stories
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.29,0:12:07.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,for "just between you and me" stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:12.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the reality is it's a sad world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.16,0:12:14.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if it's the director of the show,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.30,0:12:19.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,people would make photocopies\Nwhile he's sleeping,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.17,0:12:24.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,or he's put in a room where\Nthe heater isn't even working.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.51,0:12:27.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted people to know a little about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.84,0:12:30.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that's it for the inside stories...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.20,0:12:43.17,sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)\blur5\4c&HF7F603&\c&HFFF9BF&\t(0,1200,\4c&H47801F&\c&H00000&)}Please tell us about\Nthe 'Mushishi' opening
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.85,0:12:39.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was already thinking about using\NIchigo Sugawara-san's published photos
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.19,0:12:47.11,dialogue,,0,0,0,,for the opening from the planning phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.13,0:12:52.13,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The finished opening created\Nby combining those photos
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.47,0:12:57.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,with the acoustic guitar\Nmusic by Ally Kerr-san
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.47,0:13:02.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,was something that greatly\Nexceeded my expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.15,0:13:09.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I was aiming to create was\Nsomething that starts late at night
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.13,0:13:11.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,as if it's flowing in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.82,0:13:15.97,dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I thought about people\Nwho stay up that late,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.97,0:13:24.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought there wouldn't be that many\Nwho routinely stay up that late.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.62,0:13:26.90,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I think the viewers would be divided
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.90,0:13:29.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,into those who were\Nlooking forward to the show,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.95,0:13:33.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,or those who happened\Nto have that channel on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.51,0:13:41.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,For those who were looking\Nforward to it, I wanted them to think,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.65,0:13:46.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Whoa, it's really starting" when they see\N"Original Story by Yuki Urushibara".
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.79,0:13:51.79,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that even those who knew\Nthe manga very well would be excited
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.63,0:13:59.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,when they see an opening that has\Ndrawings of nothing in particular
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.85,0:14:05.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and doesn't hint at all at the content\Nof the show that is about to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.14,0:14:11.14,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hoped that they'd wonder\Nwhat the show would be like.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.56,0:14:16.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, for those who happened to be\Ntuning in, I wanted them to think,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.80,0:14:23.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"For some reason, I like this," or\N"There is something about this opening."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.83,0:14:29.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter if they only saw\N"Original Story by Yuki Urushibara"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.16,0:14:37.72,dialogue,,0,0,0,,or they saw only the title "Mushishi"\Nand even changed the channel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.72,0:14:42.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was hoping that the person who\Nchanged the channel would ask someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.04,0:14:47.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I don't know if it's a\Nvariety show or a drama,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.95,0:14:52.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I saw a show titled "Mushishi"\Nlate at night. What's that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.12,0:14:56.02,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or he/she would check it in a search\Nengine on the Internet and find out,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.02,0:15:01.02,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Oh, that was anime?" or\N"Oh, there's a manga for this."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.80,0:15:05.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope that people would start watching\Nthe show with those things as an entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.08,0:15:17.06,sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)\blur5\4c&HF7F603&\c&HFFF9BF&\t(0,1200,\4c&H47801F&\c&H00000&)}Please tell us about\Nthe 'Mushishi' endings
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.13,0:15:09.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each "Mushishi" episode
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.54,0:15:13.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,is different from the others;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.81,0:15:16.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,some episodes have\Nhappy endings, others don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.88,0:15:20.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,An episode about sea\Nand an episode about mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.48,0:15:28.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew from the planning phase that\Nit'd be difficult to use the same ending
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.34,0:15:31.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,for all these episodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.23,0:15:38.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I asked Masuda-san if he\Ncould create different music
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.10,0:15:42.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,for each episode as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.84,0:15:49.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masuda-san gladly accepted saying,\N"Why don't I? Let's do all the episodes."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.68,0:15:56.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"After all, I agree that it wouldn't work if\Nwe use the same music for each episode."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.67,0:15:59.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is how it came to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.12,0:16:05.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally, I think it's almost impossible\Nto make these things happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.81,0:16:10.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't think of a good way to describe it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.70,0:16:15.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the music he created\Nfor each ending is just incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.99,0:16:18.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the ending of each episode, I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.32,0:16:21.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This is great music.\Nit's well-suited for this episode."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.09,0:16:26.71,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I know that's just natural\Nsince Masuda-san created the music
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.71,0:16:29.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,specifically for that episode,\Nbut you know what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.48,0:16:34.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masuda-san likes the manga\Nvery much, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.34,0:16:40.01,dialogue,,0,0,0,,When speaking of ideals, I think\Nsomething incredible is being created.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.01,0:16:43.65,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm feeling that it\Ndidn't have to be this good,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.65,0:16:50.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I'm just amazed that something\Nthis incredible could come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.99,0:16:53.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.69,0:17:05.34,sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)\blur5\4c&HF7F603&\c&HFFF9BF&\t(0,1200,\4c&H47801F&\c&H00000&)}What do you want to convey\Nthrough 'Mushishi'?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.78,0:17:00.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I want to convey...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.78,0:17:02.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel that it's not something
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.38,0:17:04.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,that I should say myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.12,0:17:09.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think this is a show that gives\Na different impression to people
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.94,0:17:15.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,depending on their situation, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.28,0:17:19.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,students who are preparing\Nto take school entrance exams,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.10,0:17:22.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,people who have just moved,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.17,0:17:27.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,people who have just\Naccepted the job offer, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:29.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think the manga is like that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.48,0:17:37.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if you ask me if there's something that\NI want to convey, it's a little different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.49,0:17:43.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want them to feel something.\NI'm hoping to convey something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.49,0:17:45.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anything. It doesn't matter what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.74,0:17:50.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can be little things, such as\N"I don't know why but it made me cry," or
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.10,0:17:55.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I don't know why, but it made me\Nreally want to see the rural scenery,"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.97,0:17:58.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,or "It made me want to go to the sea," etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.11,0:18:04.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want people to feel\Neven little things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.11,0:18:14.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What makes me the happiest is\Nwhen they want to watch it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.46,0:18:19.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want them to feel like,\N"I want to watch it again,"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.53,0:18:24.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,or "I guess I'll bring out the DVDs and try\Nwatching it again in several years," etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.47,0:18:29.65,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a show that gives you\Na different impression
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.67,0:18:33.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,depending on the feelings\Nyou have at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.47,0:18:37.90,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if you watch it again\Nafter a long interval,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.90,0:18:43.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,this series will probably continue\Nto stay alive during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.15,0:18:48.93,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm hoping that this will\Nbecome a series like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.38,0:18:53.04,title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(573.545,152.727)\fad(900,0)\bord5\blur20}Mushishi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.38,0:18:53.04,ep-title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(900,0)\bord5\blur10}From the Director to the Viewers
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.10,0:19:00.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think this is a wonderful show that\Nis very faithful to the original work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.79,0:19:06.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, how should I put it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.49,0:19:12.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like if you way Ginko feels about things
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.46,0:19:16.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,like how relaxed he is throughout the series
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.87,0:19:20.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,when you watch the DVDs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.51,0:19:22.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
